The paper discusses a method for compressing and managing time series data, which is a common topic in database research (cs.DB). The use of models and algorithms for efficient query processing also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes a set of primitives for efficiently describing correlation, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The use of Apache Spark and Apache Cassandra suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability and extensibility of the proposed method, which is a common topic in systems research (cs.SI).
